<TITLE> Three students washed away in Cox's Bazar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazar, July 26 (bdnews24.com)  Three students went missing after being swept out to sea in Cox's Bazar Saturday, a police official said. Cox's Bazar superintendent of police Banaj Kumar Mojumder told bdnews24.com that 11 friends went bathing at the Laboni point of the sea beach around 1 am. Witnesses said a strong tide swept away seven people. Locals rescued four people but three went missing, the police officer said. Two people were taken to local hospital. The missing people were identified as Robayet Hossain Rushdi, 20, a student of Independent University, Chittagong campus, Chittagong Islamic University student Rifat Hossain Shaon, 21, and Sunshine College HSC candidate Rubel Dash. Cox's Bazar Model Police Station chief AKM Mohiuddin said the tourist spot lacked adequate manpower and equipment to launch an instant rescue effort. Didarul Alam, a photographer for The Independent, who was an eyewitness to the tragedy, told bdnews24.com: "The students went far away from the beach during the high tide." bdnews24.c
